  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="KT61-kilavi">tōḻi talaimakaṉ vāyilkaṭku uraittatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">Declared to HIS mediator by the confidante.</p>
          </div>



        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="KT61">
<l>                taccaṉ ceyta ciṟumā vaiya</l>
<l>                mūrntiṉ puṟāa rāyiṉuṅ kaiyi</l>
<l>                ṉīrttiṉ puṟūu miḷaiyōr pōla</l>
<l>                vuṟṟiṉ puṟēe māyiṉu naṟṟērp</l>
<l>                poykai yūraṉ kēṇmai</l>
<l>                ceytiṉ puṟṟaṉeñ ceṟintaṉa vaḷaiyē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
             <l rend="indent">Like boys who have pleasure in pulling with the hand</l>
             <l rend="indent">the little horse-cart made by the carpenter,</l>
             <l rend="indent">even if they can't have the pleasure of mounting [it],</l>
             <l>we had the pleasure of having made friends with the man</l>
             <l rend="indent4">from a pond village</l>
             <l rend="indent">with good chariot, even if we don't have the pleasure we had.<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uṟṟu</term>: the absolutive is a problem here. We expect <term xml:lang="ta">uṟṟa</term>, the <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term>.</note></l>
             <l>[Our] bangles have stayed tight.</l>


             
                </lg>
        </div>
